# Project Structure

All source code lives under `src/`. Follow this layout strictly.

```
src/
├── app/                          # Next.js App Router (pages & layouts only)
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                       # Small, reusable "dumb" components (Button, Input, Badge)
│   └── features/                 # Complex "smart" components (WorkerMap, BookingModal)
├── hooks/                        # Custom React hooks (useGeolocation, useSupabaseAuth)
├── services/                     # Pure logic for external APIs (supabaseClient, googleMapsService)
├── types/                        # TypeScript interfaces and types
└── middleware.ts
```

## Rules

- **`components/ui/`** — stateless or minimal-state presentational components. No API calls.
- **`components/features/`** — composed components that wire hooks + ui together. May subscribe to data.
- **`hooks/`** — any reusable `useState`/`useEffect` logic extracted from components.
- **`services/`** — framework-agnostic modules that talk to Supabase, Google Maps, etc. No React imports.
- **`types/`** — shared TypeScript types/interfaces. One file per domain (`database.ts`, `maps.ts`).
- **`app/`** — route pages and layouts only. Keep page files thin; delegate to `components/features/`.
